  "storyline": "# Storyline\n\n## Context\n\nSchedule and ticket-volume data lived in separate relational and NoSQL stores, making peak-load bottlenecks invisible in standalone reporting.\n\n## Workflow\n\nHybrid data modeling → API-driven cross-system connectivity → ratio-metric analysis → Tableau operational dashboards.\n\n## Technical Implementation\n\n- **Modeling:** relational + NoSQL scheduling data with MySQL and MongoDB into a hybrid query layer.\n- **Connectivity:** API-driven DB connectivity across distributed systems; query-response analysis showed ~30% improvement at peak load.\n- **Analysis:** train-to-ticket ratio metrics exposed a ~20% peak-hour shortfall.\n- **Dashboards:** 2+ Tableau views of congestion and capacity gaps.\n\n## Outcomes\n\nTranslated query-layer output into peak-load schedule recommendations, giving stakeholders a visual lens on operational bottlenecks."
